Increase ci (#889)

* Change MTU size of BLE transfer packets

This change allows us to monkeypatch the increase in MTU size to
optimize the data transfer rate. Currently, we are setting it at
505, which is the limit the android can accept.

* Allow for Changing the Connection Interval

This change allows us to change the connection interval through
system calls when we obtain the connection handle. It's hacky,
but it accomplishes the task. It's important to note a few things.
First, the Bluetooth specs require that a connection interval as low
as 7.5 ms. Second, there is a 1.25 multiplier on the min & max
settings.

Merge pull request #887 from iankchristie/fileServing

File serving

Allow Fatbeacon to serve large files

This change allows the Fatbeacon to serve large files, as opposed to
one message that is less than the mtu size. The central will call
the same characteristic until it receives a packet size smaller
than the mtu. The peripheral will slice the message and serve the
next slice when the central askes for it.

Merge pull request #885 from iankchristie/GATTStart

Gatt start

Add webpageCharacteristic for Beacon to Read

This change adds a webpageCharacteristic, with a UUID already known to the
central, for the central to read html content from. It creates a fully
connectable GATTservice that sends back a very simple message.

Conflicts:
	nodejs/FatBeaconPeripheral/FatBeacon.js

Merge pull request #881 from iankchristie/FatBeaconStart

Add FatBeacon Implementation for Eddystone

Add FatBeacon Implementation for Eddystone

This change sets up an eddystone-beacon to advertise a fatbeacon. It
uses monkey-patching to override dependent functions at runtime, in
order to attatch the Fatbeacon header. It is not connectable, as it
contains no service or characteristic to read from.

Send URL initially to PWS before Broadcasting

This change sends Url to PWS to comply with chrome sanitization. This
also removes some of the object fields and instead passes data as
parameters.

Merge pull request #877 from iankchristie/gzipFatBeacon

Gzip fat beacon

Add detection and decompression of gzip info

This change uses the presence of a Descriptor UUID, collected at
service-discovery time, to determine if the contents of streamed data
are gzipped. If they are, then it will decompress the file and
present it to the user.

Merge pull request #594 from cco3/desc

Add title and description fields to PwsResult
Add title and description fields to PwsResult

Share data directly between Fragment and Service

Instead of subscribing to every detailed update, the fragment now
shares data directly with the service and receives notices when
any data has changed.  This simplifies the interactions between the
two, paving the way for a shared Collection (when we integrate the
collections library).

One aspect of this change is that it replaces the fragments
mPwoMetadataQueue with an mUrlQueue.  This is simplier for checking
whether new urls are already stored in the queue, but it also will
allow us to access the most appropriate metadata at the time of
display, as opposed to at the time of placing the data into the
queue.

Deserialize to UrlDevice, not to specific subclass

The UrlDeviceJsonSerializer is designed to serialize a specific
subclass of UrlDevice and de serialize a specific subclass of
UrlDevice.  We should not dictate what it deserializes to, only what
it deserializes from.  This will allow updated versions of clients to
transition between subclasses of UrlDevice.

Merge pull request #435 from cco3/display

Show urls in batches

[android] Fine-tune url display behavior

Previous behavior:

- 3s:   sort and show all urls, stop scanning

New behavior:

- 2s:   sort and show all urls
- 5s:   sort and show all new urls beneath the first set
- 5+s:  show each new url at bottom of list
- 10s:  stop scanning

[android] Consolidate start/stop code in Fragment

There's a lot of duplicate logic in the fragment for starting and
stopping a scan.  By consolidating them, we will make it easier to
replace this with new scanning code.

[android] Safe start/stop mdns discovery

The NsdManager likes to complain if we start or stop it while it is
already in the desired state.  This change turns our
start/stopScanning methods into safe methods that check the state of
the scanner before performing the operation.

signals in the future.  If the requests includes multiple values, they
will be sorted on the server automatically.  However, this rank value is
useful for merging separate replies from multiple independant metadata
requests on the client.

Fix one source of config disconnect problem

The MainActivity is using a fragment stack on a container for About and
Config but a different stack on a different container for
NearbyDevices. The result is a missing onPause call when entering
BeaconConfigFragment. This kept the BLE scan running at LOW_LATENCY.
Scanning and GATT connections cannot occur at the same time so this was
causing a problem.
